<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="O" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Overhear" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Overhear</orth> (cf. <emph>O'erhear</emph>) 1) to hear without being spoken to: <bibl n="shak. mm 3.1.161" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 1, 161</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 1.2.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado I, 2, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 3.1.6" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.241" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 241</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.95" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 95</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.187" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 187</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.3.26" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 3, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.639" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 639</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.4.74" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 4, 74</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.2.103" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 2, 103</bibl>.<lb />2) to hear again, or to hear from beginning to end: <cit><quote>and --d what you shall o.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.95" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 95</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>